name: DeKalb County (GA) Board of Health
tweet: @SheilaDecker19 @AshleySWeitz @GaDPH @GNRHealth @CDCgov We'll admit, this is an awkward position, as we're at the end of the chain of command. Yesterday's DPH media release touches on the info flow and what to expect:  https://t.co/sL1KUHa83j

name: DeKalb County (GA) Board of Health
tweet: @SheilaDecker19 @AshleySWeitz @GaDPH @GNRHealth @CDCgov We don't make our own guidance. Guidance flows from CDC, to GaDPH, to the health districts (us). We cannot begin vaccination until we receive ALL of the clinical guidance and GaDPH gives us the green light to begin. As much as we'd like it to be, it's not an instant process.

name: DeKalb County (GA) Board of Health
tweet: @AshleySWeitz @jessica_pyper @GaDPH @GNRHealth @CDCgov We truly appreciate everyone bearing with us, considering the "awkward" position we find ourselves in at the bottom of the chain. üòá We're ready to get going, but DPH ultimately gives us the green light.
